name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Twins are on the board after Goodwin overthrows the cutoff man and the ball gets away from (bounces off of) both Rod√≥n and Collins at home plate. Runner comes home from third and slides around Rod√≥n's tag attempt.  Sox lead trimmed to 3-1.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Sox say it's a bruised right hand for Moncada, who is being further evaluated.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Liam Hendriks and Josh Donaldson were teammates with the Blue Jays in 2015. Let's just say that Donaldson's behavior toward the Sox the last few days hasn't changed Hendriks' opinion of the guy.  "I am not a Donaldson fan."  https://t.co/BmDb6xvChL

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Moncada is out of the game after the apparent wrist issue running the bases in the third inning. Andrew Vaughn is at third base for the Sox.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Sox get another run on a Sheets sac fly. And what looked to be an inning-ending double play is avoided when umps rule that Donaldson got in the way of Grandal's return trip to second base.  It's 3-0 in the third.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: And scores on a Grandal base hit. It's a 2-0 Sox lead.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: He's staying in the game.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Moncada takes an ugly looking slide into third base when motoring there from first on an Abreu single. Looks like he landed funnily on his right wrist. Trainer giving him a long looksee.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Gavin Sheets smokes an opposite-field double off the left-field wall. His hot start continues.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Brian Goodwin with his second homer in as many days. Did you know he is hitting .318 with two homers, a double, four walks and seven runs scored in his last seven games? Pretty good!

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: A terrific double play by Andrelton Simmons cancels the stew. Fabulous defense there by the Twins shortstop.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Sox got a stew goin' in their half of the first, Moncada and Jos√© Abreu putting two on with back-to-back one-out singles.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Carlos Rod√≥n strikes out Miguel San√≥ to get out of it with no runs on the board. He threw 28 pitches in the first inning. "London Calling" plays. Don't know why, but I'm all for it.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Yo√°n Moncada has had trouble at third base in the first inning. Couldn't get a grounder out of his glove, leading to an infield hit. Now an error as a grounder eats him up.  Tiles totaled with Twins.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: He walks, ending his first-inning homer streak this series. I mean, unless the Twins are gonna send 11 guys to the plate this inning.

tweet: Yasmani Grandal on the Josh Donaldson stuff:  "It didn't go unnoticed. ... If anything, thanks to him for getting us awakened a little bit."

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: And this ballgame is ovah. Donaldson talked, Donaldson homered, then the Sox blasted the Twins, 13-3. Sox hit six homers, including two by Grandal. The offensive cure they craved during that losing stretch? Facing the Twins, apparently.  They go for the sweep tomorrow afternoon.

name: Vinnie Duber
tweet: Because eight home runs were not enough for one game, the Twins have contributed the night's ninth. It does little to impact the score, which is now 13-3, in favor of the Sox, in the eighth inning.
